a%20from%20Flightradar24%20shows%20that%20just%20over%20an%20hour%20into%20the%20journey%20and%20cruising%20at%2037%2C000%20feet%2C%20the%20Boeing%20737%20turned%20south%20and%20diverted%20to%20Tulsa%2C%20Oklahoma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FgmIup%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20of%20the%20US%20shows%20the%20flight%20path%20of%20Southwest%20Flight%202665%20on%20May%2011%20which%20departed%20Albuqerque%20and%20diverted%20to%20Tulsa%2C%20Oklahoma%2C%20instead%20of%20continuing%20to%20Baltimore.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FgmIup%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%20involved%2C%20registered%20as%20N265WN%2C%20is%20over%2019%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20said%20the%20airplane%20landed%20safely%20%26quot%3Bafter%20the%20crew%20reported%20a%20cracked%20windshield.%26quot%3B%20It%20added%20that%20it%20would%20investigate%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouthwest%20Airlines%20said%20the%20flight%20%26quot%3Bdiverted%20safely%20to%20Tulsa%20due%20to%20a%20windshield%20crack.%26quot%3B%20It%20added%20that%20the%20flight%20landed%20%26quot%3Buneventfully%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20passengers%20were%20put%20on%20another%20airplane%20to%20Baltimore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20appreciate%20the%20professionalism%20of%20our%20Flight%20Crew%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20airline%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlightradar24's%20data%20shows%20the%20replacement%20airplane%20reached%20Baltimore%20around%2011%3A30%20p.m.%20%E2%80%94%20four%20hours%20later%20than%20passengers%20initially%20expected%20to%20arrive%20in%20the%20Maryland%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20isn't%20yet%20clear%20what%20caused%20the%20windshield%20to%20crack%2C%20those%20on%20board%20would%20have%20been%20at%20very%20little%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlane%20windshields%20are%20designed%20with%20several%20layers%2C%20including%20tempered%20glass%20and%20other%20materials%2C%20so%20that%20they%20can%20still%20function%20safely%20in%20case%20any%20individual%20layer%20is%20damaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20October%2C%20a%20United%20Airlines%20jet%20saw%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fntsb-probing-how-united-airlines-windscreen-cracked-in-midair-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewindshield%20cracked%20by%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20weather%20balloon%20while%20flying%20at%2036%2C000%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20bird%20strikes%20are%20more%20common%20than%20a%20weather%20balloon%20or%20space%20debris%2C%20it%20is%20still%20very%20rare%20for%20them%20to%20damage%20an%20airplane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20that%20month%2C%20a%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpete-hegseths-flight-diverts-due-to-cracked-windshield-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eairplane%20carrying%20Pete%20Hegseth%3C%2Fa%3E%20U-turned%20over%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%20after%20its%20windshield%20cracked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20notorious%20windshield%20incident%20occurred%20in%201990%20when%20a%20British%20Airways%20pilot%20was%20partially%20ejected%20from%20the%20airplane.%20The%20crew%20held%20him%20in%20place%2C%20and%20he%20survived%20with%20frostbite%20and%20some%20fractures.%20However%2C%20this%20was%20not%20caused%20by%20a%20cracked%20windshield%2C%20but%20rather%20because%20it%20was%20installed%20with%20the%20incorrect%20screws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouthwest-airlines-suffers-cracked-windscreen-and-forced-to-divert-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778589783000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a03168cba7