%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-causes-inflation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20annual%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20accelerated%20more%20than%20expected%2C%20with%20the%20consumer%20price%20index%20rising%203.8%25%20in%20April%20from%20a%20year%20ago.%20Economists%20expected%20a%203.7%25%20increase%2C%20and%20it's%20the%20highest%20inflation%20rate%20since%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fktpeg%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%20of%20the%20percent%20change%20of%20the%20consumer%20price%20index%20from%20the%20previous%20year%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fktpeg%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ECPI%20increased%200.6%25%20from%20March%2C%20as%20expected%2C%20and%20was%20cooler%20than%20March's%200.9%25%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20inflation%20spike%20is%20starting%20to%20hit%20workers'%20wallets%20and%20outpace%20wage%20growth.%20Real%20earnings%20dropped%20by%200.5%25%20over%20the%20month%20and%20were%20down%200.3%25%20over%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECore%20CPI%2C%20which%20excludes%20volatile%20food%20and%20energy%20prices%2C%20increased%202.8%25%20from%20a%20year%20ago%20in%20April%2C%20just%20above%20the%20forecast%20of%202.7%25%20and%20the%20previous%202.6%25%20increase.%20Core%20CPI%20increased%200.4%25%20from%20March%2C%20more%20than%20the%20previous%200.2%25%20and%20the%20forecast%20of%200.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnergy%20prices%20increased%2017.9%25%20year%20over%20year%2C%20the%20largest%20increase%20since%20September%202022.%20More%20specifically%2C%20gas%20prices%20increased%2028.4%25%20year%20over%20year.%20Energy%20prices%20rose%203.8%25%20month%20over%20month%2C%20cooler%20than%20March's%2010.9%25%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAAA%20data%20showed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmap-compares-gas-price-state-us-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egas%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20climbed%20to%20around%20%244.50%20on%20average%20from%20just%20under%20%243%20at%20the%20end%20of%20February%20when%20the%20Iran%20war%20started.%20Prices%20at%20the%20pump%20are%20likely%20leading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgas-prices-worsening-k-shaped-economy-research-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elower-income%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20modify%20their%20gas%20consumption%2C%20while%20higher-income%20households%20are%20mostly%20trucking%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHigher-income%20households%20have%20reduced%20real%20gas%20consumption%20only%20modestly%20and%20increased%20gasoline%20spending%20considerably%20compared%20with%202023%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%20post%20said%2C%20based%20on%20spending%20data%20through%20March.%20%26quot%3BIn%20contrast%2C%20lower-income%20households%20increased%20spending%20by%20much%20less%20and%20decreased%20real%20consumption%20by%20much%20more%2C%20potentially%20by%20carpooling%20or%20substituting%20to%20public%20transit%20where%20available.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGas%20prices%20are%20also%20likely%20taking%20a%20toll%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgas-prices-shape-americans-feelings-economy-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople's%20feelings%20about%20the%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20consumer%20sentiment%20index%20dropped%20to%20a%20record%20low%20of%2048.2%20in%20May%2C%20based%20on%20preliminary%20data%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMiddle%20East%20developments%20are%20unlikely%20to%20meaningfully%20boost%20sentiment%20until%20supply%20disruptions%20have%20been%20fully%20resolved%20and%20energy%20prices%20fall%2C%26quot%3B%20Joanne%20Hsu%2C%20the%20surveys%20of%20consumers%20director%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECME%20FedWatch%2C%20which%20shows%20traders'%20expectations%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-meeting-interest-rates-fomc-jerome-powell-april-live-updates-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed's%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20showed%20a%20more%20than%2090%25%20chance%20that%20interest%20rates%20will%20be%20held%20steady%20at%20the%20next%20scheduled%20meeting%20in%20mid-June%2C%20which%20will%20be%20the%20first%20under%20a%20new%20Fed%20chair.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20that%20inflation%20is%20heading%20in%20the%20wrong%20direction%20and%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20holding%20up%2C%20it's%20very%20unlikely%20that%20the%20Fed%20will%20be%20able%20to%20lower%20interest%20rates%20any%20time%20soon%20and%20it's%20possible%20that%20we%20may%20start%20pricing%20in%20rate%20hikes%20for%20next%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chris%20Zaccarelli%2C%20chief%20investment%20officer%20for%20Northlight%20Asset%20Management.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Warsh%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20confirmed%20as%20Jerome%20Powell's%20successor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20exists%20for%20one%20fundamental%20purpose%3A%20to%20foster%20the%20economic%20conditions%20in%20which%20American%20families%20and%20businesses%20can%20thrive%20%E2%80%94%20stable%20prices%2C%20a%20strong%20job%20market%2C%20and%20a%20financial%20system%20they%20can%20depend%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said%20at%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20press%20conference%20in%20April.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20decision%20we%20make%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20about%20interest%20rates%2C%20or%20regulatory%20and%20supervisory%20matters%2C%20or%20other%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20is%20made%20in%20service%20of%20that%20purpose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcpi-inflation-april-consumer-price-index-202