22%20alt%3D%5C%22Louisa%20Rogers%20and%20her%20husband%20in%20Guanajuato%2C%20Mexico%2C%20on%20top%20of%20a%20hill.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fddfb9ba7ef34b41f36513%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20and%20her%20husband%20live%20about%20half%20the%20year%20in%20Guanajuato%2C%20Mexico.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Louisa%20Rogers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20bought%20our%20house%20in%20Guanajuato%2C%20Mexico%2C%2020%20years%20ago.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20spend%20about%20half%20the%20year%20there.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20walk%20all%20the%20time%20when%20I'm%20there%20and%20have%20become%20fluent%20in%20Spanish.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20my%20husband%20went%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiking-trek-ecuador-quilotoa-loop-with-husband-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree-hour%20hike%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20hill%20called%20Cruz%20Azul%2C%20above%20Guanajuato%2C%20the%20Mexican%20city%20where%20we%20live%20about%20half%20the%20year.%20When%20we%20left%2C%20we%20simply%20locked%20our%20door%20and%20started%20walking.%20We%20love%20that%20without%20getting%20into%20a%20car%20or%20a%20bus%2C%20we%20can%20be%20hiking%20in%2020%20minutes%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20many%20health%20benefits%20of%20living%20in%20Guanajuato.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bf0f869a-5468-45d6-8482-e3951e7d3a45%5C%22%3ELiving%20here%20is%20great%20for%20my%20physical%20health%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20our%20home%20is%20so%20central%2C%20we%20come%20and%20go%20frequently%20throughout%20the%20day.%20We%20don't%20have%20a%20car%2C%20and%20don't%20want%20one.%20Guanajuato's%20row%20houses%20don't%20have%20garages%20or%20driveways%2C%20and%20parking%20lots%20are%20pricey%2C%20which%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-changing-american-car-culture-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efew%20people%20have%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Having%20no%20other%20option%20but%20to%20walk%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20stay%20fit%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20city%20so%20vibrant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWherever%20I%20go%20in%20town%20%E2%80%94%20to%20shop%2C%20visit%20friends%2C%20do%20yoga%2C%20go%20to%20a%20concert%2C%20or%20go%20to%20my%20Spanish%20class%20%E2%80%94%20I%20always%20walk%2C%20and%20I%20never%20object%2C%20because%20it's%20such%20a%20pleasure.%20Street%20life%20in%20Guanajuato%20is%20filled%20with%20rhythm%20and%20movement.%20I'm%20usually%20on%20a%20pedestrian%20street%2C%20where%20I%20hear%20the%20sound%20of%20musicians%20performing%20and%20pass%20vendors%20selling%20tamales%2C%20cut-up%20fruit%2C%20and%20corn%20on%20the%20cob.%20I'll%20see%20the%20medieval-dressed%20%3Cem%3Eestudiantinas%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20selling%20tickets%20for%20the%20evening%20tours%20they%20lead%2C%20strolling%20through%20different%20neighborhoods%2C%20singing%20and%20playing%20instruments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221892%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Colorful%20houses%20and%20a%20girl%20crossing%20the%20street%20on%20the%20pedestrian%20street%20where%20the%20author%20lives%20in%20Guanajuato%2C%20Mexico.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fde003e1443b8dc48e32c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221418%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20pedestrian%20street%20where%20the%20author%20lives%20in%20Guanajuato%2C%20Mexico.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Louisa%20Rogers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20anywhere%20is%20great%20for%20physical%20health%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20at%20high%20elevations%20(the%20elevation%20of%20the%20city%20is%207%2C000%20feet)%2C%20it's%20even%20better%2C%20because%20it%20forces%20the%20body%20to%20work%20harder%2C%20which%20improves%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheart-disease-take-control-cardiovascular-heart-health-early-young-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecardiovascular%20health%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Especially%20the%20first%20day%20I'm%20back%2C%20while%20adjusting%20to%20the%20altitude%2C%20I%20definitely%20feel%20it!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20of%20Guanajuato%20is%20very%20hilly.%20Many%20of%20the%20small%20streets%20are%20narrow%2C%20winding%2C%20steep%20alleys%2C%20of%20which%20there%20are%20more%20than%203%2C000.%20I%20love%20wandering%20along%20them%2C%20and%20sometimes%20I%20still%20get%20lost%2C%20because%20I%20have%20a%20poor%20sense%20of%20orientation.%20This%20doesn't%20worry%20me%2C%20because%20eventually%20I%20recognize%20a%20landmark%20and%20figure%20out%20where%20I%20am.%20I%20was%20delighted%20to%20find%20out%20that%20getting%20lost%20is%20actually%20good%20for%20mental%20health%2C%20because%20it%20stimulates%20the%20part%20of%20the%20brain%20responsible%20for%20spatial%20navigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20I%20work%20out%20with%20two%20kettlebells%20and%20a%20stability%20ball%2C%20and%20three%20mornings%20a%20week%2C%20I%20walk%2025%20minutes%20to%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-yoga-tips-longtime-yogi-things-wish-i-knew-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoga%20class%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Because%20it's%20taught%20in%20Spanish%2C%20the%20class%20benefits%20not%20only%20the%20body%20but%20also%20the%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eaee63d9-253d-4efb-9584-141f53578226%5C%22%3EIt's%20good%20for%20my%20mind%2C%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%2020%20years%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fim-bilingual-was-made-fun-of-because-accent-growing-up-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudying%20Spanish%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I'm%20now%20fluent%2C%20though%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20I%20don't%20make%20mistakes.%20I%20have%20a%20weekly%20Spanish%20teacher%20who%20corrects%20my%20errors%2C%20explains%20the%20never-ending%20Mexican%20%3Cem%3Emodismos%3C%2Fem%3E%20(slang)%2C%20and%20serves%20as%20an%20interpreter%2C%20helping%20me%20to%20understand%20and%20decode%20the%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENavigating%20another%20culture%20is%20also%20good%20for%20the%20brain.%20This%20week%2C%20I%20asked%20my%20teacher%20a%20question%20related%20to%20cultural%20etiquette.%20In%20Mexico%2C%20people%20use%20titles%20much%20more%20than%20in%20the%20US%2C%20because%20showing%20respect%20is%20very%20important.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20evening%20view%20from%20the%20author's%20balcony%20in%20Mexico.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fde01fc9dd4cb81cda879c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22467%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20evening%20view%20from%20the%20author's%20balcony%20in%20Mexico.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Louisa%20Rogers%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20when%20I%20asked%20my%20yoga%20teacher%20if%20I%20should%20call%20her%20%26quot%3BMaestra%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BYolanda%2C%26quot%3B%20her%20name%2C%20she%20replied%20with%20her%20name.%20This%20made%20sense%20to%20me%2C%20since%20I'm%20older%20than%20she%20is%2C%20thus%20partly%20equalizing%20us.%20But%20I%20noticed%20in%20our%20WhatsApp%20group%20that%20the%20other%20participants%20all%20addressed%20her%20by%20her%20title%2C%20so%20I%20felt%20awkward%20using%20her%20name.%20My%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fage-gap-friendship-spanish-teacher-generational-differences-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpanish%20teacher%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20I%20call%20her%20%26quot%3BMaestra%20Yola%26quot%3B%20(short%20for%20Yolanda)%20%E2%80%94%20a%20balance%20of%20formality%20and%20informality.%20Tricky!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-abroad-expat-singapore-opportunity-far-from-home-guilt-aging-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiving%20in%20another%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%20benefits%20not%20only%20brain%20function%20but%20also%20emotional%20well-being%20and%20mental%20health.%20As%20a%20friend%20who%20suffered%20from%20depression%20before%20moving%20to%20Guanajuato%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20forget%20you're%20depressed%20when%20you're%20focusing%20on%20the%20Spanish%20subjunctive.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20when%20I%20was%20grieving%20my%20father's%20death%2C%20I'd%20sit%20on%20our%20patio%20and%20practice%20pronunciation%2C%20repeating%20%3Cem%3Epotta%20tea%2C%20potta%20tea%2C%20potta%20tea%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20soft%20English%20%3Cem%3Et%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20is%20a%20way%20station%20to%20%3Cem%3Epara%20ti%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20Spanish%20%3Cem%3Er%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Practicing%20the%20Spanish%20%3Cem%3Er%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Err%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehelped%20me%20focus%20on%20something%20other%20than%20my%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarry%20and%20I%20knew%20we%20loved%20Guanajuato%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20we%20decided%20to%20buy%20our%20house%2C%20but%20we%20had%20no%20idea%20that%20living%20here%20would%20help%20us%20stay%20so%20physically%20and%20mentally%20healthy%20as%20we%20aged.%20Now%2C%20at%2083%20and%2074%2C%20we%20think%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20smartest%20decisions%20we've%20ever%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flive-part-time-mexico-good-health-benefits-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778588221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fddfb9ba7ef34b41f36513%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flive-part-time-mexico-good-health-benefits-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20husband%20and%20I%20live%20about%20half%20the%20year%20in%20Mexico.%20We%20got%20our%20house%20there%20about%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20it's%20been%20good%20for%20my%20body%20and%20mind.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22louisarogers51%40gmail.com%20(Louisa%20Rogers)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22c