20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EMouni%20Roy%20has%20built%20a%20significant%20financial%20empire%2C%20with%20an%20estimated%20net%20worth%20between%20Rs%2040-41%20crore.%20Her%20wealth%20stems%20from%20television%2C%20Bollywood%20films%20like%20'Brahm%C4%81stra'%2C%20endorsements%2C%20and%20digital%20collaborations.%20The%20actress%20enjoys%20a%20luxurious%20lifestyle%2C%20owning%20premium%20Mumbai%20apartments%20and%20expensive%20cars%2C%20including%20Mercedes%20models.%20Her%20high%20fees%20for%20projects%20further%20solidify%20her%20strong%20financial%20standing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22James%20Gunn%E2%80%99s%20Superman%20Sequel%3A%20Sinqua%20Walls%20joins%20Man%20of%20Tomorrow%3B%20role%20kept%20under%20wraps%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778588034000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-131039053%2Cimgsize-225164.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fhollywood%2Fnews%2Fsinqua-walls-joins-james-gunns-man-of-tomorrow-as-superman-sequel-films-in-atlanta-report%2Farticleshow%2F131039039.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F131039039.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ESinqua%20Walls%20is%20officially%20part%20of%20the%20ensemble%20cast%20for%20'Man%20of%20Tomorrow%2C'%20the%20much-anticipated%20Superman%20sequel%20directed%20by%20James%20Gunn%2C%20which%20is%20now%20underway%20in%20Atlanta.%20Though%20details%20about%20his%20role%20remain%20secret%2C%20Walls%20will%20share%20the%20screen%20with%20David%20Corenswet%20portraying%20Superman%20and%20Nicholas%20Hoult%20as%20the%20infamous%20Lex%20Luthor.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20could%20hollow%20out%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20workers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Participants%20during%20a%20Hackathon%20session%20at%20a%20developer%20event%20organized%20by%20OpenAI%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20India%2C%20%20in%20January%202026.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a02f306ba7ef34b41f37470%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETom%20Slater%20warned%20that%20overreliance%20on%20AI%20could%20erode%20the%20skills%20workers%20need%20to%20build%20real%20expertise.%3Cp%3ESamyukta%20Lakshmi%2FBloomberg%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETom%20Slater%20said%20AI%20could%20hollow%20out%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20skilled%20workers%20by%20eroding%20their%20skills.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20investor%20said%20workers%20still%20need%20struggle%20and%20repetition%20to%20build%20expertise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESlater%20warned%20short-term%20AI%20productivity%20gains%20may%20create%20long-term%20skill%20erosion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20may%20make%20young%20workers%20faster%20and%20more%20productive%2C%20while%20also%20quietly%20stopping%20them%20from%20becoming%20experts%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20warning%20from%20Tom%20Slater%2C%20the%20manager%20of%20Scottish%20Mortgage%20Investment%20Trust%20and%20a%20partner%20at%20Baillie%20Gifford%2C%20who%20said%20that%20companies%20embracing%20AI%20too%20aggressively%20risk%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-gen-z-job-killer-or-opportunity-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehollowing%20out%20the%20pipeline%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20trains%20future%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BMerryn%20Talks%20Money%26quot%3B%20podcast%20on%20Monday%2C%20Slater%20said%20that%20unless%20we%20invest%20in%20the%20next%20generation%20and%20ensure%20that%20they%20learn%20foundational%20and%20analytical%20skills%2C%20businesses%20could%20end%20up%20with%20workers%20who%20know%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20tools%20but%20lack%20the%20foundational%20expertise%20needed%20to%20judge%20whether%20the%20output%20is%20actually%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20concern%20echoes%20that%20of%20AI%20researchers%20and%20some%20tech%20leaders%20who%20have%20warned%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-deskilling-impact-on-worker-skills-productivity-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eoverreliance%20on%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20gradually%20erode%20the%20very%20skills%20workers%20need%20to%20perform%20and%20think%20critically%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInnovation%20theorist%20John%20Nosta%20said%20AI%20is%20training%20humans%20to%20think%20backward%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-human-intelligence-impact-at-work-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egiving%20polished%20answers%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20people%20fully%20understand%20them.%20AI%20researcher%20Vivienne%20Ming%20said%20that%20most%20users%20are%20relying%20on%20AI%20to%20think%20for%20them%20rather%20than%20using%20it%20to%20deepen%20their%20reasoning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlater%20said%20that%20younger%20employees%20need%20to%20struggle%20through%20difficult%20tasks%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eat%20work%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20develop%20expertise.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20would%20just%20get%20better%20at%20using%20AI%2C%20but%20you%20will%20confuse%20that%20with%20thinking%20that%20you're%20good%20at%20the%20actual%20topic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlater%20pointed%20to%20research%20suggesting%20that%20overreliance%20on%20AI%20can%20weaken%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cited%20an%20MIT%20study%20from%20last%20June%20that%20tracked%2054%20participants%20over%20four%20months%20and%20found%20that%20people%20who%20used%20ChatGPT%20to%20write%20essays%20showed%20lower%20brain%20engagement%20and%20often%20struggled%20to%20remember%20or%20quote%20from%20work%20they%20had%20produced%20only%20minutes%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20AI%20improves%20short-term%20productivity%20while%20quietly%20weakening%20long-term%20capability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20dynamic%20could%20create%20a%20dangerous%20incentive%20for%20employers%2C%20he%20suggested.%20Companies%20can%20save%20money%20by%20reducing%20entry-level%20hiring%20and%20leaning%20more%20heavily%20on%20AI%20systems%2C%20but%20Slater%20believes%20that%20strategy%20amounts%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20to%20me%20very%20shortsighted%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20allowing%20the%20current%20generation%20of%20experienced%20professionals%20to%20use%20these%20tools%20to%20get%20a%20%26quot%3Bproductivity%20bump%26quot%3B%20without%20thinking%20about%20the%20next%20generation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlater%20compared%20the%20issue%20to%20pilots%20learning%20to%20fly%20manually%20before%20relying%20on%20autopilot%20systems.%20Professionals%2C%20he%20said%2C%20still%20need%20to%20develop%20deep%20expertise%20before%20AI%20can%20genuinely%20enhance%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20will%20thrive%20are%20not%20those%20who%20use%20AI%20the%20most%2C%26quot%3B%20Slater%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20those%20who%20can%20still%20think%20without%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-impact-on-young-workers-skills-brain-atrophy-expert-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778587996000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a02f31ce1443b8dc48e422e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-impact-on-young-workers-skills-brain-atrophy-expert-2026-5%22%2C%22summary